<F P=100> BOSNIA-HERZEGOVINA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Muslims Violate Cease-Fire in Sarajevo </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Muslims Violate Cease-Fire in Sarajevo </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0906090794 Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service in 
Serbo-Croatian 0829 GMT 9 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0906090794 </F>
<F P=104>  Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service </F>
<F P=105>  Serbo-Croatian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpts] Sarajevo, 9 Jun (TANJUG) -- Muslim forces 
violated the cease-fire on the Sarajevo front last night by 
opening sniper fire on Serbian defense lines, wounding one 
civilian and one Serbian soldier, the information center of the 
Sarajevo-Romanija corps announced this morning. [passage omitted] 
  Last night Serbian reconaissance units sighted a column of 
vehicles moving along the Mt. Igman-Hrasnica road. It is said 
that the vehicles were transporting military equipment for the 
Muslim army, with the tacit approval of the UN Protection Force. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

