<F P=100> POLAND </F>
<H3> <TI>   Sejm Adopts Resolution on Arms Exports </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Sejm Adopts Resolution on Arms Exports </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0906091294 Warsaw PAP in Polish 0833 GMT 9 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0906091294 </F>
<F P=104>  Warsaw PAP </F>
<F P=105>  Polish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Warsaw, 9 Jun--The Sejm today adopted a resolution 
urging the government to restrict the so-called negative list, 
concerning the export of weapons and military equipment, to 
countries covered by the UN embargo. The issue was discussed at 
the previous Sejm session, but no decision was made then due to 
the lack of a quorum. 
  The negative list is secret and includes countries to which 
the sale of weapons by the Polish arms industry has been banned. 

</TEXT>

