<H3> <TI>   Duray Hopes Hungary Continues Antall's Policy </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Duray Hopes Hungary Continues Antall's Policy </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU0806194294 Bratislava PRAVDA in Slovak 4 Jun 94 p 12 </F>
<F P=103> AU0806194294 </F>
<F P=104>  Bratislava PRAVDA </F>
<F P=105>  Slovak </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [TA SR report: "Duray Still Hopes"] </F>
  [Text] Budapest--Miklos Duray, chairman of the Coexistence 
Movement, sent a congratulatory letter to all Hungarian parties 
that had won enough votes in the elections to get into the new 
Hungarian parliament. He expressed the hope that, in the years 
to come, all Hungarian deputies would adopt a more responsible 
attitude toward the 15 million Hungarians and would continue 
without disruption to implement the consolidated [jednotna] 
Hungarian policy. In the opinion of Duray, one can therefore 
"rightly expect that each Hungarian government will consider it 
its duty to support ideas formulated by the legitimate 
representatives of Hungarians living abroad, in the same way 
Antall's government did." In contrast to other ethnic Hungarian 
politicians, Duray addressed his congratulations to all 
parliamentary parties and not to the chairman of the victorious 
Hungarian Socialist Party (MSZP). 

</TEXT>

