<H3> <TI>   Greece Allegedly Proposes New Country Name </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Greece Allegedly Proposes New Country Name </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU0906112094 Skopje MILS-NEWS in English 9 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU0906112094 </F>
<F P=104>  Skopje MILS-NEWS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Unattributed report: "Central Balkan Republic of Macedonia"] </F>
  [Text] Despite statements by [U.S. Special Envoy] Nimetz 
on bringing no proposal on the name, A1 Television cites 
unofficial circles on speculations with an alleged proposal by 
the Greek Foreign Minister Papoulias that Macedonia [The Former 
Yugoslav Republic of Macedonia -- FYROM] be referred to as The 
Central Balkan State of Macedonia. Sources suggest Papoulias 
has sent this proposal to the Macedonian authorities through the 
envoy Nimetz, and go on claiming that PASOK [Panhellenic 
Socialist Movement] is all ready to accept the name of 
Macedonia, and the Greek Government is more inclined to the 
latest proposal than to the prefix "North" or "New" Macedonia. 

</TEXT>

