<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Moravcik: Early Elections `Extremely Necessary' </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU0806173494 Bratislava SMENA in Slovak 4 Jun 94 p 2 </F>
<F P=103> AU0806173494 </F>
<F P=104>  Bratislava SMENA </F>
<F P=105>  Slovak </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [TA SR report: "Do We Have a Firm Grip on It?"] </F>
  [Excerpts] Bratislava--In an interview for Slovak Radio, 
Prime Minister Jozef Moravcik described the early elections in 
the Slovak Republic as extremely necessary. As far as the 
crisis in parliament is concerned, he is of the opinion that the 
Movement for a Democratic Slovakia is to blame for the 
situation. [passage omitted] 
  In the interview, Moravcik also responded to a REUTER report 
on the problems within the Slovak banking system. According to 
him, the Slovak Government will take measures to ensure that the 
situation depicted in the agency's inaccurate report does not 
arise. He described the banking system as the economy's nervous 
system. The Slovak Government intends to keep it in order. 
"Everything indicates that we have a firm grip on the situation 
and that there is no danger," he said. 

</TEXT>

