<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Tirana, June 3 (ATA) -- President Berisha and 
Speaker of the Macedonian Parliament Andov said yesterday that 
important steps have been made in the relations between the two 
countries and that the two parties are engaged in further 
developing cooperation and understanding between them. 
  Berisha said that Albania is interested in Macedonia's [The 
Former Yugoslav Republic of Macedonia -- FYROM] stability. "We 
encourage the Albanians that they should be a factor of 
stability for Macedonia, just as we insist that the recognition 
of human and national rights of the Albanians residing there 
serves the stability of the Macedonian state itself. In this 
context, mutual respect between the Albanians and Macedonians is 
of specific importance," President Berisha said. 
  Mr. Andov appreciated the Albanian policy in the Balkans as 
well the facilities Albania has created to Macedonia to cope 
with the Greek embargo. He demanded from President Berisha 
Albania's support for Macedonia's membership of CSCE, the Black 
Sea initiative as well as other institutions, whose member 
Albania is. President Berisha assured the speaker of the 
Macedonian Parliament that Albania will support Macedonia's 
membership of CSCE as well as its membership in the Black Sea 
initiative. "I consider the enlargement of the Black Sea 
initiative with a new member as a very significant moment," he 
said. 

</TEXT>

