<F P=100> ANNEX </F>
<F P=101> Slovakia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Poll Reflects Public Attitudes on Joining NATO </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Poll Reflects Public Attitudes on Joining NATO </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU0706123794 Prague CTK in English 1029 GMT 7 Jun 94 -- FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> AU0706123794 </F>
<F P=104>  Prague CTK </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Bratislava, June 7 (CTK) -- Less than a half of 
Slovak citizens favor the idea of Slovakia's joining NATO, 
according to a poll conducted by the Slovak Statistical Office 
in May. 
  Only 15 percent of those questioned said it was most 
necessary for Slovakia to try to join NATO, while 34 percent 
believed that it was probably necessary. Almost one Slovak out 
of five (18 percent) is afraid and 11 percent are sure that such 
efforts are senseless. 22 percent of those polled did not answer 
the question. 
  If Slovakia became a member of NATO, almost two fifths of 
citizens (37 percent) would expect an improvement in Slovakia's 
defense capability, according to the poll. Four percent of 
Slovaks said they would expect the defense capability to worsen. 

</TEXT>

