<H3> <TI>   Klaus: ODS Supports Establishing Senate </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Klaus: ODS Supports Establishing Senate </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU0706084594 Prague CTK in English 1844 GMT 6 Jun 94 -- FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> AU0706084594 </F>
<F P=104>  Prague CTK </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Prague June 6 (CTK) -- "The Civic Democratic Party 
(ODS) Executive Council confirms that the ODS has supported in 
the past and is unambiguously supporting the establishment of 
the Senate on the majoritarian principle in accordance with the 
Czech Constitution," ODS Chairman and Czech Premier Vaclav Klaus 
said today. Speaking to journalists during a break in an 
Executive Council meeting, Klaus added that the ODS Deputies' 
Group had proceeded from this principle while discussing the 
bill on the senatorial elections. 
  He said the council had resolutely rejected the 
unsubstantiated statements about a non-constitutional state 
which had allegedly arisen in the Czech Republic. "Nothing of 
the kind is true. I see no signs of the constitutional crisis 
which would justify an urgent need for change in the Czech 
Constitution," Klaus said. 
  He described as a "fully false card produced by some 
political parties" statements about the non-constitutional state 
in the Republic and proposals by some deputies that if the 
Senate is not established some of its powers should be 
transferred to the president. Klaus pointed to the existing 
temporary provisions in the Constitution which "clearly say how 
competences are being divided up to the moment when the Senate 
appears." "We permanently respect the Constitution and the 
majoritarian principle on which the Senate should be set up and 
we believe it will be filled at a proper moment," Klaus said. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

