<H3> <TI>   Government Approves Debt Agreement With Russia </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Government Approves Debt Agreement With Russia </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU0906094394 Prague CTK in English 1849 GMT 8 Jun 94 -- FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> AU0906094394 </F>
<F P=104>  Prague CTK </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Prague June 8 (CTK) -- The Czech Government today 
approved the debt repayment agreement with Russia closed on May 
30 by the Czech deputy finance minister, Premier Vaclav Klaus 
told journalists after a cabinet meeting. The agreement 
concerns the repayment of $3.5 billion of Russian debts to the 
Czech Republic by the year 2003. 
  "The Government considers this agreement to be a remarkable 
success and is content with this one bird in the hand, for the 
two fat ones weren't so much in the bush as up in the clouds," 
said Klaus. He mentioned the fact that the Czech negotiators 
had succeeded in fixing the amount of the debt, interest rate 
conditions, an exact term of specific repayments, and a 
one-to-one exchange rate of the rouble to the dollar. 
  Klaus specified that the agreement means the Czech Republic 
will receive $52 million this year, $101 million the next and 
$391 million in 1996. He said that it had been clear from his 
April meeting with Russian Premier Viktor Chernomyrdin in Moscow 
that the debt would not be repaid with oil or gas. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

