  [Text] Prague June 9 (CTK) -- The cancellation of the 
clearing account for trade between the Czech and Slovak 
Republics would be no big problem for the Czech Republic from 
the viewpoint of foreign currency reserves, but may create a 
problem for both sides as regards the volume of trade, Czech 
Finance Minister Ivan Kocarnik said today. Kocarnik was 
responding on NOVA Television to yesterday's statement by Slovak 
Economy Minister Peter Magvasi that the clearing account had 
outlived its usefulness. He told CTK that payments ought to be 
liberalised which meant trading in convertible currencies. 

</TEXT>

