<F P=102>   LD0906184994 Warsaw PAP in English 1712 GMT 9 Jun 94 -- FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> LD0906184994 </F>
<F P=104>  Warsaw PAP </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Warsaw, June 9 -- Head of the National Radio and TV 
Council Ryszard Bender signed on Thursday a licence to broadcast 
nationally for the Warsaw-based Radio "Zet" station. The 
station is the second private radio station, along with the 
"RMF" radio from Krakow, that will air programmes nationwide. 
Bender told a press conference that he hopes that the licence 
for the third non-public radio station, the Catholic "Maryja" 
radio, will be signed next week. 
  Owner of the Radio "Zet" station Andrzej Wojciechowski said 
that his radio would change its programmes and start as a 
completely new station. He also said that on Thursday afternoon 
his radio will start broadcasting a special signal, inaudible to 
human ear, that will act as a repellent to mosquitoes. The 
signal will resemble sounds emitted by bats. 

