<F P=101> Poland </F>
<H3> <TI>   Pawlak, Officials Receive Delegation </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Pawlak, Officials Receive Delegation </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU0906151394 Tirana ATA in English 1021 GMT 9 Jun 94 -- FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> AU0906151394 </F>
<F P=104>  Tirana ATA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Tirana, June 9 (ATA) -- A delegation of the 
Albanian Parliament headed by Pjeter Arbnori, speaker of the 
parliament, is on a visit to Poland at the invitation of the 
speaker of the Sejm of the Polish Republic, Jozef Oleksy. The 
delegation has had meetings with the Polish minister of foreign 
affairs, Andrzej Olechowski, Premier Waldemar Pawlak, and 
leaders of various parliamentary parties. 
  Mr. Arbnori and his delegation visited the city of Krakow in 
which they talked about the experience in local governing and 
the city of Czestochowa, which has established sister relations 
with the city of Shkoder, northern Albania. In Czestochowa Mr. 
Arbnori talked about cooperation in the field of education. 
Albanian delegation also visited the church Jasna Gora, a 
centre of pilgrimage for believers of various religion 
throughout the world. 

</TEXT>

