<H3> <TI>   Spanish UN Force Opens River Route to Sarajevo </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Spanish UN Force Opens River Route to Sarajevo </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1006120694 Madrid RNE International in Spanish 1000 GMT 10 
Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1006120694 </F>
<F P=104>  Madrid RNE International </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The Spanish Blue Helmets deployed in Bosnia on a 
peace mission have reopened the Neretva River route after three 
months of hard work. Slovak Blue Helmets deployed in the area 
also took part in this mission. 
  The reopening of the route means that the link between the 
Dalmatian coast and the Bosnian capital, Sarajevo, has been 
reestablished. A floating bridge has been installed on the 
Bijela River to replace the one destroyed during the fighting 
between Croats and Muslims. 
  The UK's Michael Rose, commander of the Blue Helmets in the 
area, was at the bridge-opening ceremony where a plaque was 
unveiled in honor of the Blue Helmets, among whom are the 
Spaniards belonging to the Cordoba Group. 

</TEXT>

