<F P=103> LD0906221794 </F>
<F P=104>  Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network </F>
<F P=105>  Serbo-Croatian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Ejup Ganic, member of the Bosnia-Herzegovina 
Presidency and vice president of the Bosniak-Croat Federation, 
who led our country's delegation at the talks in Geneva, 
returned to Sarajevo this afternoon. Upon his arrival Ejup 
Ganic gave a brief statement on the cease-fire agreement: 
  [Begin Ganic recording] We have done what the assembly asked 
us to do. As far as Gorazde and the talks on the four-week 
cease-fire are concerned, we did not agree to freeze [the 
positions] that the aggressors tried to impose on us with help 
from some UN circles, and we tried to decide on what was best 
for our country. 
  I must say straight away that some new ideas exist. If the 
arms embargo is not lifted there should be a reduction in 
armament. [end recording] 

