<F P=100> BOSNIA-HERZEGOVINA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Serb Attacks Reported Despite Cease-Fire </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Serb Attacks Reported Despite Cease-Fire </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1006105594 Zagreb Radio Croatia Network in Serbo-Croatian 
1000 GMT 10 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1006105594 </F>
<F P=104>  Zagreb Radio Croatia Network </F>
<F P=105>  Serbo-Croatian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] A one-month cease-fire that was agreed in Geneva is 
coming into effect in Bosnia-Herzegovina at this very moment. 
However, reports coming from the front lines do not speak of 
peace. 
  As regards the Brcko area, Serb artillery attacks have been 
in progress since last night against civilian targets in 
Boderiste and deep into the free territory. Reconnaissance 
units of the 108th Infantry Brigade of the Croatian Defense 
Council [HVO] of Brcko have reported that Serb tank 
reinforcements were being brought into the southeastern part of 
the Brcko area. 
  As regards the Orasje-Samac area, the Serb aggressor engaged 
in provocations from small infantry weapons, the Orasje 
operative zone of the HVO reported. They said that the Serb 
Army was continuing to bring in reinforcements south of the 
so-called corridor around Krepsic and Pelagicevo. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

