<H3> <TI>   Granic Meets With Bosnian Federation's Ganic </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Granic Meets With Bosnian Federation's Ganic </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0906210694 Zagreb Radio Croatia Network in Serbo-Croatian 
1700 GMT 9 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0906210694 </F>
<F P=104>  Zagreb Radio Croatia Network </F>
<F P=105>  Serbo-Croatian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Mate Granic, Croatian deputy prime minister and 
foreign minister, has received in Zagreb Ejup Ganic, a member of 
the Bosnia-Herzegovina Presidency and vice president of the 
Bosnia-Herzegovina Federation. 
  Ejup Ganic informed Minister Granic about the Geneva peace 
talks, which resulted in a one-month cease-fire in 
Bosnia-Herzegovina. He stressed that representatives of the 
Bosniak and Croat nations in the Federation's delegation 
coordinated their activities during the talks. Ganic expressed 
thanks for the great assistance of the Croatian mission at the 
UN in Geneva. 
  Minister Granic told his guest about the steps Croatia will 
undertake in order to peacefully reintegrate its occupied areas 
into the constitutional and legal system of the Republic of 
Croatia. 

</TEXT>

