<F P=106> [Statement from the Office of the President of the Republic </F>
of Croatia -- read by announcer] 
  [Text] President Tudjman today received Muhamed Zulic, a 
deputy of the Croatian Assembly, in the presence of Jure Radic, 
the HDZ [Croatian Democratic Union] secretary general. With 
regard to the situation in the assembly, Deputy Zulic said he 
continues to be an HDZ member, adding that he will explain to 
the public the misunderstandings in connection with his joining 
the Croatian Independent Democrats. 
  They also spoke about the implementation of the Washington 
agreement. In this connection, Mr. Zulic said that both as an 
HDZ deputy and as a Croat of the Muslim religion, he wishes to 
take an active part in the implementation of the Washington 
agreement and to work on building trust between the Croats and 
Muslims. 

</TEXT>

