<H3> <TI>   Constitutional Court Asked To Reinstate Mesic </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Constitutional Court Asked To Reinstate Mesic </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0906180494 Zagreb Radio Croatia Network in Serbo-Croatian 
1500 GMT 9 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0906180494 </F>
<F P=104>  Zagreb Radio Croatia Network </F>
<F P=105>  Serbo-Croatian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Stjepan Mesic has lodged a protest with the Croatian 
Constitutional Court, requesting the protection of his 
constitutional rights. Mesic suggests that the Constitutional 
Court should annul the decision of the Chamber of Deputies of 
the Assembly of 24 May this year, whereby the president 
[speaker] of the chamber was relieved of duty. The protest note 
was received in the Constitutional Court today, and Stjepan 
Mesic's office distributed it to journalists in the Croatian 
Assembly. 
  In his protest note Mesic explained why he postponed the 
18th 
session of the Chamber of Deputies and stressed that, when the 
president was relieved of duty, provisions of the Constitution 
and the Chamber's code of practice--that is, the constitutional 
rights of the speaker of the chamber and the procedure for 
adopting documents on relieving him of duty--were violated. 

</TEXT>

