<F P=104>  Skopje MILS-NEWS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Unattributed report: "Close to Reaching Terms"] </F>
  [Text] Macedonia [The Former Yugoslav Republic of 
Macedonia -- FYROM] and Greece are close to reaching terms of 
agreement, the Macedonian Foreign Minister Stevo Crvenkovski 
stated for the weekly magazine PULS. He pointed out Macedonia's 
view, insisted on from the beginning, on a need to resolve 
problems in a package and establish long-term and sound friendly 
relations, is accepted not only by the other side but by the 
international community as well. As for the two-day talks with 
U.S. envoy Nimetz, Crvenkovski said they focused on the next 
round of negotiations on ministers level, due next week in New 
York. 

