<F P=100> ANNEX </F>
<F P=101> Albania </F>
<H3> <TI>   Investigation Phase Ends in Alia Trial </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Investigation Phase Ends in Alia Trial </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU0906144794 Tirana ATA in English 1019 GMT 9 Jun 94 -- FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> AU0906144794 </F>
<F P=104>  Tirana ATA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Tirana, June 9 (ATA) -- Yesterday's seance of the 
trial against the 10 former high communist functionaries marked 
the end of the phase of the judicial investigation. In the 
beginning of the seance, the chief judge, Andi Celiku, called 
witness Sulejman Abazi, taking into consideration the request 
made by the defence attorney of the defendant Zylyftar Ramizi. 
Witness Abazi testified on the platform of the operative work in 
the organs of the former Interior Ministry, and also on the 
incident in Qafa e Barit. 
  The chief judge stated that the other witnesses, who have 
been called, have had healthy reasons or have been abroad. The 
jury decided that their testimonies be read in the Prosecutor's 
Office. Prosecutor Fana read the testimonies of 16 witnesses 
who did not come to this seance. The next seance will be on 
June 11. 

</TEXT>

