<F P=100> HUNGARY </F>
<H3> <TI>   Szekeres Wants Old, New Faces in Government </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Szekeres Wants Old, New Faces in Government </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1006105994 Budapest Kossuth Radio Network in Hungarian 
1000 GMT 10 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1006105994 </F>
<F P=104>  Budapest Kossuth Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Hungarian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The new government will also have members who have 
already gained experience in the Miklos Nemeth government, said 
Imre Szekeres, [executive deputy chairman of the Hungarian 
Socialist Party, MSZP], speaking to the "Napteve" program. At 
the same time the MSZP executive deputy chairman added that 
those younger experts and politicians who have only recently 
become known in the MSZP will also be considered in the course 
of the distribution of portfolios. The most important 
qualification in the ministerial appointments will be 
suitability, Imre Szekeres confirmed. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

