<H3> <TI>   Horn Sends Message to Hungarians in Romania </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Horn Sends Message to Hungarians in Romania </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU1006152994 Budapest MAGYAR HIRLAP in Hungarian 10 Jun 94 p 
3 </F>

<F P=103> AU1006152994 </F>
<F P=104>  Budapest MAGYAR HIRLAP </F>
<F P=105>  Hungarian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Gyula Horn, chairman of the Hungarian Socialist 
Party [MSZP], replied with a warm message to the congratulatory 
letter sent to him by Bela Marko, executive chairman of the 
Democratic Union of Hungarians in Romania [RMDSZ -- UDMR in 
Romanian], MAGYAR HIRLAP was informed by the office of the RMDSZ 
chairman. 
  Expressing thanks for the good wishes expressed on behalf of 
the RMDSZ, Horn pointed out in his letter that his party has 
always followed with great attention and sympathy the "heroic 
struggle of the RMDSZ for the survival of the ethnic Hungarians 
living in Romania and the full assertion of their individual and 
community rights," and that the MSZP has endeavored to support 
all this with their available means. Gyula Horn assured Bela 
Marko and the RMDSZ of the fact that "supporting the vital 
autonomy efforts of the Hungarians living beyond the borders" is 
one of the outstanding goals of the Socialists' government 
program. The MSZP is determined to do everything in its power 
to successfully assert this in the increased government 
responsibility of the party. Gyula Horn expressed his hope that 
he would be soon able to discuss the issue of "effective 
RMDSZ-MSZP cooperation" personally with Bela Marko. 

</TEXT>

