<F P=100> YUGOSLAVIA </F>
<F P=101> Federal </F>
<H3> <TI>   FRY To Respond to `Any Kind' of Aggression </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    FRY To Respond to `Any Kind' of Aggression </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1206124894 Belgrade TANJUG in English 1225 GMT 12 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1206124894 </F>
<F P=104>  Belgrade TANJUG </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> ["Pool" item] </F>
  [Text] Kragujevac, June 12 (TANJUG) -- Yugoslav Defence 
Minister Pavle Bulatovic said on Sunday that the defensive 
capability of the Federal Republic of Yugoslavia (F.R.Y.) was 
well maintained despite the big problems and all objective 
hardships caused by the two-year-old international sanctions. 
  Bulatovic, in an interview to Radio Kragujevac, Serbia, 
pointed out that the Army of Yugoslavia had a highly developed 
system of the country's defences. 
  "It is common knowledge," said he, "that Yugoslavia does not 
have any territorial claims on any of its neighbours, but it is 
ready to respond to aggression of any kind." He confirmed that 
some of the neighbour states were launching provocations along 
the Yugoslav borders, counting on external support. This, as he 
said, was nothing new, because they used to do the same whenever 
they thought Yugoslavia was weakened by internal troubles and by 
pressures exerted by the big powers. 
  Asked about the danger of Yugoslavia's being involved in 
war, 
with reference to NATO violations of Yugoslavia's airspace, 
Bulatovic said that ``no one in his right mind has any interest 
in involving Yugoslavia into a war, as this would widespread the 
war conflagration in the Balkans, and it is the big question 
whether (the war) would be limited to this area alone. 
  "Every impartial observer may realize that Serbia and 
Montenegro, that is, the Federal Republic of Yugoslavia, had not 
started the war on the soil of the former Yugoslavia, and that 
they have no intention of including themselves in it. On the 
contrary, they are doing their utmost for paths to be found for 
the establishment of just and lasting peace in these areas," 
said Bulatovic. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

<DOC>
<DOCNO> FBIS4-31587 </DOCNO>
<HT>    "dreeu113_y_94005" </HT>


<HEADER>
