<F P=100> POLAND </F>
<H3> <TI>   Sejm Adopts Amendment Easing Antiabortion Law </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Sejm Adopts Amendment Easing Antiabortion Law </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1006200694 Warsaw PAP in Polish 1942 GMT 10 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1006200694 </F>
<F P=104>  Warsaw PAP </F>
<F P=105>  Polish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Warsaw, 10 Jun--The Sejm adopted an amendment to the 
Penal Code today that permits abortion in the event of the 
woman's "difficult living conditions or complicated personal 
situation." The act was adopted as proposed by the Parliamentary 
Women's Group and supported by more than 200 deputies. Two 
hundred and forty-one deputies voted for the act, 107 were 
against, and 32 abstained. 

</TEXT>

