Daily Report 
<DATE1>  11 Jun 1994 </DATE1>

</HEADER>

<F P=100> POLAND </F>
<H3> <TI>   SLD Wants Constitution First </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    SLD Wants Constitution First </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1106121994 Warsaw PAP in Polish 1114 GMT 11 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1106121994 </F>
<F P=104>  Warsaw PAP </F>
<F P=105>  Polish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Warsaw, 11 Jun--The Democratic Left Alliance [SLD] 
parliamentary floor group today submitted a motion to the Sejm 
Presidium for "postponing the first reading of the bill on the 
ratification of the concordat between the Holy See and the 
Polish Republic until after a new constitution of the Polish 
Republic comes into force," group Chairman Aleksander 
Kwasniewski told journalists. Earlier it was said at the Sejm 
that the debate on the concordat would be held on 2 July. 
  Kwasniewski said that this step was not directed against the 
church or the believers, and it was not aiming at stirring up a 
war over outlooks on life. He added that it intended to lead to 
the situation when the concordat "will be freed from public 
doubts, also expressed during the campaign before the 19 
September general election." 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

