<F P=100> BOSNIA-HERZEGOVINA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Mladic on Tolerating Muslim, Croat Attacks </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Mladic on Tolerating Muslim, Croat Attacks </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1206212094 Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service in 
Serbo-Croatian 2008 GMT 12 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1206212094 </F>
<F P=104>  Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service </F>
<F P=105>  Serbo-Croatian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Sarajevo, 12 Jun (TANJUG) -- Colonel General Ratko 
Mladic, chief of staff of the army of the republic of Srpska, 
tonight told Serb Radio's Sarajevo Studio that Muslim and Croat 
forces again failed today to comply with the cease-fire on 
Bosnia-Herzegovina's front lines. The heaviest attacks on the 
republic of Srpska were launched in the Brcko area. There were 
also enemy provocations on other front lines, Mladic said. 
  "We are going to continue our full compliance with what we 
agreed to in Geneva, i.e. to refrain from offensive operations 
and we are going to tolerate their attacks as long as they are 
not a serious threat to the republic of Srpska and the Serbian 
people," the chief of staff of the army of the republic of 
Srpska said. He also said that the army of the republic of 
Srpska "will not allow enemy forces to enjoy their leisure." 
  "We are following all their efforts to consolidate their 
ranks within this month of cease-fire and to arm themselves and 
prepare offensive operations, something they hinted at even 
before their arrival in Geneva," General Mladic said. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

