<F P=100> BOSNIA-HERZEGOVINA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Six Wounded in Shelling </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Six Wounded in Shelling </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1206192394 Belgrade TANJUG in English 1914 GMT 12 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1206192394 </F>
<F P=104>  Belgrade TANJUG </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpts] Brcko, June 12 (TANJUG) -- Six people were 
wounded in an artillery shelling of the Serb town of Brcko in 
northeastern Bosnia on Sunday, the town's press centre said in 
the evening. [passage omitted] The enemy was again shelling 
civilan targets, mostly residential buildings, inflicting 
extensive damage, and only rain, which has forced most people 
off the streets, kept the number of casualties as low as it was. 
This was the eighth artillery shelling of Brcko in the last 
month, and fifth from the direction of Croatia. A total of 
seven people were killed and 46 others were wounded in the 
attacks. The local U.N. observer team has duly informed the 
Tuzla-based command of the U.N. Protection Force (UNPROFOR) for 
northeastern Bosnia and the UNPROFOR command in Sarajevo of each 
incident, lodging protests. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

