<H3> <TI>   Abdic Forces Continue Attacks </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Abdic Forces Continue Attacks </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU1306110394 Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network in 
Serbo-Croatian 1000 GMT 13 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> AU1306110394 </F>
<F P=104>  Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network </F>
<F P=105>  Serbo-Croatian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by Mirza Sadikovic from Bihac] </F>
  [Excerpts] Early this morning Mayor Mirsad Crnkic, 
commander of the 511th Glorious Bosanska Krupa Brigade, died 
after being shot [words indistinct] on the front line by a 
maverick bullet from the positions of Abdic's rebels and 
traitors. [passage omitted] 
  Since early this morning the members of Abdic's rebel 
paramilitary have been shelling the areas of Pecigrad, Skokovi, 
Todorovo, Golubovici, (Pljanici), and (Krivaja). They have 
attempted several infantry breakthroughs, thus proving that 
their warmongers are not giving up on further conflicts 
regardless of the means and human cost. Since yesterday they 
have destroyed dozens of houses and inflicted several 
casualties. This is why they obviously do not want to carry out 
the agreed exchange of the bodies of killed soldiers. 
  Karadzic's chetniks have been abundantly helping out the 
Kladusa paramilitary as they have been firing with antiaircraft 
weapons and small arms throughout the night and this morning on 
the (Bihac) and Bosanska Krupa fronts. They have also 
intensified their activities on the Grmusko-Srbljanski Plateau. 
Our defenders have not been responding to these attacks in 
compliance with the arranged cease-fire. 

</TEXT>

