<H3> <TI>   Serbs Reprotedly Stop Civilians Returning Home </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Serbs Reprotedly Stop Civilians Returning Home </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU1306111994 Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network in 
Serbo-Croatian 1000 GMT 13 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> AU1306111994 </F>
<F P=104>  Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network </F>
<F P=105>  Serbo-Croatian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by Enes Musovic from Gorazde] </F>
  [Text] This morning at 0730 some 300 citizens of 
(Cazagici) and (Hudjer), districts within 3 km of the Gorazde 
center, started off by themselves toward their properties and 
homes. As they said, they could no longer bear to listen to 
daily misinformation about the chetniks having withdrawn from 
their homes. They could no longer wait for someone else to 
solve their problems, particularly as the UN Protection Forces 
[UNPROFOR] has not tried to do this in the only correct way. 
  However, they were stopped in front of the (Cazagici) 
district by a group of chetniks armed with machine guns, Osa and 
Zolja portable rocket launchers, and hand grenades, who started 
to abuse and provoke them while at the same time cocking their 
guns. Very soon UNPROFOR positioned in Gorazde intervened with 
transporters and a large number of soldiers, thus barring the 
citizens of (Hudjer) and (Cazagici) from reaching their homes. 
The situation turned very tense, but the [word indistinct] 
authorities prevented the unarmed people at the last moment from 
charging at the chetnik barrels. 
  It is obvious to everyone in Gorazde that the zone of three 
km from the city center has not been cleared, that the Serbian 
civilians are in fact Serb soldiers, and that they have remained 
in all their positions within this zone. All in all, the 
situation here is very tense and the likelihood of incidents and 
bloodshed seems to be increasing by the minute. 
  Victor Andreyev, chief of the UNPROFOR civilian section in 
Bosnia-Herzegovina, was informed about this on 7 June when he 
visited Gorazde. However, UNPROFOR has done nothing about it, 
and is still deceiving the world with tales that the Serbian 
soldiers, Serbian police, and Serbian civilians have left the 
3-km zone from the center of Gorazde. 

</TEXT>

