<H3> <TI>   CSSD Deputy To Chair BIS Commission </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    CSSD Deputy To Chair BIS Commission </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU1006142194 Prague LIDOVE NOVINY in Czech 4 Jun 94 p 3 </F>
<F P=103> AU1006142194 </F>
<F P=104>  Prague LIDOVE NOVINY </F>
<F P=105>  Czech </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Article by "(has)": "An Opposition Deputy Has Become Head </F>
of the Parliamentary Commission for the Security and Information 
Service"] 
  [Text] Prague--The reason Tomas Svoboda (Christian 
Democratic Party), chairman of the parliamentary commission for 
supervising the Security and Information Service (BIS), has 
resigned is apparently that he does not have enough time to 
execute his post. Svoboda has told LIDOVE NOVINY that "nothing 
more serious happened" and that he will carry on as deputy 
chairman of the commission. In connection with the anticipated 
discussion on the recall of T. Fejfar (Civic Democratic Party), 
deputy chairman of the Defense and Security Committee, Svoboda 
categorically rejected the possibility that he could take up 
this post. He described as speculation the CTK report that he 
aspires to the post of committee deputy chairman. The new 
chairman of the commission is current Deputy Chairman V. 
Doubrava (Czech Social Democratic Party) [CSSD]. In reply to a 
question on what he thinks of the fact that an opposition deputy 
chairs the commission for supervising the secret service, 
Svoboda said that "Doubrava is very objective." 

</TEXT>

