<F P=100> POLAND </F>
<H3> <TI>   National Security Head Resigns; Successor Named </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    National Security Head Resigns; Successor Named </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1306173194 Warsaw Radio Warszawa Network in Polish 1700 
GMT 13 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1306173194 </F>
<F P=104>  Warsaw Radio Warszawa Network </F>
<F P=105>  Polish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] This evening Minister Jerzy Milewski asked President 
Lech Walesa to release him from the duties of National Defense 
Committee secretary and the responsibility of heading the 
National Security Bureau attached to the president's 
chancellery, which is legally linked to them. 
  Lech Walesa has accepted the resignation and appointed 
Henryk 
Goryszewski to these posts, and simultaneously appointed him 
also secretary of state in the Chancellery of the President of 
the Polish Republic. 

</TEXT>

