<F P=100> POLAND </F>
<H3> <TI>   TV, Defense Ministry Sign Agreement </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    TV, Defense Ministry Sign Agreement </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1406101294 Warsaw PAP in Polish 0827 GMT 14 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1406101294 </F>
<F P=104>  Warsaw PAP </F>
<F P=105>  Polish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Warsaw, 14 Jun (PAP)--In Warsaw today, National 
Defense Minister Piotr Kolodziejczyk and Wieslaw Walendziak, 
chairman of Polish Television SA [joint-stock company], signed 
an agreement on cooperation in the production and broadcasting 
of television programs on defense and military issues. Military 
programs are to become more attractive. 
  Kolodziejczyk told journalists that the agreement will 
enable 
the presentation of issues related to the Army "in a flexible 
way and in response to need, and not according to a rigid 
schedule." He added: "I think that a battle for television 
slots is a misunderstanding." 
  Walendziak explained that military programs will be produced 
with "technological contribution from the Army". He said: "I am 
pleased about the agreement because there has been a lot of 
discussion recently about whether television is willing to 
cooperate with state institutions. Of course, it is willing, 
provided these institutions clearly express their expectations. 
The Ministry of National Defense is the first ministry to say 
very clearly what hopes it attaches to cooperation with 
television, and which has not tried to do this in a dictatorial 
manner," he said. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

