<H3> <TI>   VMRO-DPMNE: Authorities Purging Police </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    VMRO-DPMNE: Authorities Purging Police </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU1306125294 Skopje MILS-NEWS in English 13 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU1306125294 </F>
<F P=104>  Skopje MILS-NEWS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Unattributed report: "VMRO-DPMNE Public Announcement"] </F>
  [Text] In its announcement for the public, VMRO-DPMNE 
[Internal Macedonian Revolutionary Organization-Democratic Party 
for Macedonian National Unity] most bitterly criticized latest 
staff purges in the Interior Ministry, which turn the ministry 
into a committee of protection of the current ruling coalition, 
especially SDSM [Social Democratic Alliance of Macedonia] and 
the Liberal Party. Mr. Gogov's [former deputy head of the 
Interior Ministry Operative Department] press conference clearly 
showed police leaders Frckovski [minister of internal affairs], 
Bogoevski [undersecretary in the intelligence service], and 
Gjurev must leave immediately. Fabricating political processes 
against innocent people was a feature of totalitarian 
Stalinist-communist regimes, but Macedonia is obviously not 
immune to this. Democracy and human rights are continually 
being narrowed by the current true dictatorship, the 
announcement says. The party demands that the Interior Ministry 
officially explain the role of the recently killed high 
inspector Dimce Ristovski in revealing a crime including over a 
million German marks, with a presumable involvement of the 
minister of health, Jovan Tofovski. The party also appealed to 
Pavle Trajanov, in the name of democracy and the future of the 
Macedonian state, to publicly reveal government's attempts to 
discredit him in the eyes of the public, and state other 
fabricated cases, as well as the government involvement in 
organized crime in the country. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

