<H3> <TI>   Institute Reports on Economic Performance </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Institute Reports on Economic Performance </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU1306123194 Skopje MILS-NEWS in English 13 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU1306123194 </F>
<F P=104>  Skopje MILS-NEWS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Unattributed report: "Statistics Information"] </F>
  [Text] The State Statistics Institute reports a 8.6 
percent productivity decrease in April as compared to the same 
period last year. The April inflation is 2.4 percent, and 
living costs rose by 2.6 percent. The number of employed 
citizens in March was 405,610, with an average wage 7,497 
denars. There were 180,644 unemployed, or 0.8 percent more than 
in the previous month. In the first four months of the year, 
the total exports fell by 13.1 percent in comparison to last 
year (the exports totalled $233.7 million), while imports 
increased by 8.7 percent (total of $261.8 million). Public 
consumption goods are mostly imported (the import of these goods 
increased by 85.5 percent). 

</TEXT>

