<H3> <TI>   SDL: HZDS Preparing Anti-Kovac Referendum </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    SDL: HZDS Preparing Anti-Kovac Referendum </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU1306144994 Bratislava NARODNA OBRODA in Slovak 10 Jun 94 p 
2 </F>

<F P=103> AU1306144994 </F>
<F P=104>  Bratislava NARODNA OBRODA </F>
<F P=105>  Slovak </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [TA SR report: "A Four-Leaf Clover Is the Symbol of the </F>
Left Choice"] 
  [Text] Zvolen--The Party of the Democratic Left [SDL] has 
received indications that the Movement for a Democratic Slovakia 
[HZDS] is preparing a referendum through which it would like to 
shorten the current president's term of office. Such an attempt 
could lead to doubts being cast on Slovakia in the world and to 
new tension in Slovak society, said P. Weiss, deputy chairman of 
the National Council of the Slovak Republic [NR SR] and chairman 
of the SDL, at a meeting held in Zvolen yesterday with almost 
120 town and city mayors from Central Slovakia who were elected 
on behalf of left-wing oriented parties. Representatives of the 
election coalition--Deputy Chairman S. Krcho of the Farmers 
Movement; S. Holes, a member of the Social Democratic Party of 
Slovakia Presidium; NR SR Deputy A. Chlapikova; and others--were 
also present. 
  SDL Deputy Chairman D. Dorotin said that the left-wing 
partners agreed at the Coalition Council on Wednesday, 8 June, 
to go into the elections under the collective name of "Left 
Choice" [Lavicova volba], with a program called "Social 
Democratic and Green Choice for Slovakia," and with a green 
four-leaf clover as its symbol. The political bodies of these 
entities have still to approve the proposal. 

</TEXT>

