<F P=100> SLOVAKIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Foreign Concerns About HZDS Win Highlighted </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Foreign Concerns About HZDS Win Highlighted </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU1306150794 Bratislava SLOVENSKA REPUBLIKA in Slovak 10 Jun 
94 p 2 </F>

<F P=103> AU1306150794 </F>
<F P=104>  Bratislava SLOVENSKA REPUBLIKA </F>
<F P=105>  Slovak </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> ["(zl)"-signed and TA SR report: "The Christian Democratic </F>
Movement Is Intimidating the Voters"] 
  [Text] Bratislava--At a movement press briefing yesterday, 
Jan Carnogursky, chairman of the Christian Democratic Movement 
[KDH], said that, in conversations with him, his foreign 
partners have expressed the view that, if Meciar's Movement for 
a Democratic Slovakia [HZDS] wins the elections in Slovakia, the 
process of the Slovak Republic's integration into European 
structures will be slowed down. In reply to a question from 
SLOVENSKA REPUBLIKA on whether he thinks it is democratic for 
foreign states to influence Slovak voters, he said that these 
countries have the right of veto in admitting new members into 
the European Union and that we cannot prevent them from doing 
this. In reply to other questions from SLOVENSKA REPUBLIKA, 
which has obtained information that government members have 
increased their salaries without the agreement of parliament, he 
said that this is not true, and, in reply to a question on 
whether he thinks it is right that the government has exempted 
the daily NARODNA OBRODA from tax, he said that he knows nothing 
about it. He did not rule out the possibility of forming a 
postelection coalition with the Party of the Democratic Left. 
He said apropos of the HZDS: "A coalition with Chairman Meciar 
is not being taken into consideration for the KDH." 

</TEXT>

