<H3> <TI>   Green Party Preparing Congress, Seeking Partner </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Green Party Preparing Congress, Seeking Partner </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU1306141494 Bratislava SLOVENSKA REPUBLIKA in Slovak 9 Jun 
94 p 3 </F>

<F P=103> AU1306141494 </F>
<F P=104>  Bratislava SLOVENSKA REPUBLIKA </F>
<F P=105>  Slovak </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [TA SR report: "A Realistic Green Philosophy"] </F>
  [Text] The Slovak Green Party has been registered under 
the altered name of Slovak Green Alternative (SZA). The SZA's 
objective is to constitute the party on a realistic approach to 
green philosophy, a philosophy that will push for the optimum 
relationship between Slovakia's economic development and a 
healthy environment. This is the guarantee for a healthy and 
also socially secure individual and whole of society. The SZA 
Preparatory Committee is organizing the party's constituent 
congress on 18 June in Nitra. A decision will also be made on a 
coalition partner at the congress. The Preparatory Committee has 
held informative coalition talks with representatives from the 
Association of Slovak Workers (ZRS) and the Slovak National 
Party (SNS). Coalition talks will also be held in the near 
future with representatives of the Movement for a Democratic 
Slovakia. 

</TEXT>

