<F P=100> BOSNIA-HERZEGOVINA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Serbs See Croat-Muslim Aim To Capture Posavina </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Serbs See Croat-Muslim Aim To Capture Posavina </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1306175994 Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service in 
Serbo-Croatian 1658 GMT 13 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1306175994 </F>
<F P=104>  Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service </F>
<F P=105>  Serbo-Croatian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Brcko, 13 Jun (TANJUG) -- Bosnian Croat forces and 
the Croatian Army shelled Krepsic 10 km west of Brcko at around 
1300 today, firing twelve 82 mm mortar shells from the direction 
of Vucilovac, the press center in Brcko said today. Croatian 
forces opened strong infantry fire on Covic Polje 8 km southwest 
of Orasje from the direction of Matici at around 0900 this 
morning. 
  The republic of Srpska army units did not respond because 
the 
attacks had no serious consequences. Muslim forces also 
launched attacks on the southwestern part of the Brcko front, 
targeting Serbian positions but also without consequences for 
the Serbian side which did not respond. 
  According to Serbian military sources, the attacks indicate 
that the Croatian and Muslim forces have no intention of halting 
their operations against the Serbian defense lines in Posavina, 
and that in this way they will try to create conditions to 
realize the goal for which they have been massing troops in the 
area over the last few months -- to capture Posavina and link 
Croatian and Muslim territories through this area. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

