<H3> <TI>   Army Generals Meet Rose, View Truce Monitoring </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Army Generals Meet Rose, View Truce Monitoring </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU1306195694 Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network in 
Serbo-Croatian 1700 GMT 13 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> AU1306195694 </F>
<F P=104>  Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network </F>
<F P=105>  Serbo-Croatian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] As the Press Center of the Army of 
Bosnia-Herzegovina reports, Generals Rasim Delic and Enver 
Hadzihasanovic, commander and head of the Supreme Command of the 
Army of the Republic of Bosnia-Herzegovina respectively, had 
talks in the UN base in Visoko today with General Michael Rose, 
commander of the UN Forces for Bosnia-Herzegovina, about the 
implementation of the Geneva agreement and the method of 
monitoring the cease-fire. 
  During the meeting, the representatives of the Headquarters 
of the Supreme Command of the Army of the Republic of 
Bosnia-Herzegovina presented a proposal on the deployment of 
observers, liaison officers, as well as the way of maintaining 
mutual communications. It was agreed that in the days to come, 
heads of headquarters should establish places for deploying 
observers, as well as other elements significant for monitoring 
the cease-fire [word indistinct] in the field. 
  Army General Delic insisted that elements for monitoring the 
cease-fire with the Serbian aggressors side should be 
established in the same way and that UNPROFOR [United Nations 
Protection Force] should urgently take more efficient measures 
to stop attacks at the protected zone of Bihac, as well as to 
return the population to the right bank of the Drina River, that 
is, to the protected zone of Gorazde. 
  The (?system of) maintaining the truce on the entire 
battlefield of Bosnia-Herzegovina must be monitored in the same 
way and on the basis of the same criteria, Army General Delic 
said at the end of the talks today, it has been reported by the 
Press Center of the Army of Bosnia-Herzegovina. 

</TEXT>

